  "text": "There are 3 cellular mechanisms for the induction of programming. First, the nutrient environment may permanently alter gene expression; 1 example of this is permanent change in the activity of metabolic enzymes such as HMG-CoA reductase. [CITATION_1] Recent studies have highlighted epigenetic phenomena as a mechanism whereby the environment can influence gene expression.",
